context: <a0_0><b3_0>Soul and disco<b3_0/><a0_0/> influenced house music, plus mixing and editing techniques earlier explored by disco, garage music and post-disco DJs, producers, and <b6_0>audio engineers<b6_0/> such as <b7_0>Walter Gibbons, Tom Moulton, Jim Burgess, Larry Levan, Ron Hardy, M & M, and others<b7_0/> who produced longer, more repetitive, and percussive arrangements of existing disco recordings. <a1_0><b4_0>Early house producers<b4_0/><a1_0/> such as Frankie Knuckles created similar compositions from scratch, using <a2_0><b5_0>samplers, synthesizers, sequencers, and drum machines<b5_0/><a2_0/>.
